First, setup your GPT 1.0 environment.  You'll need to use a specific
version of the GNU autotools.  See
<http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/Divisions/NSM/GST/GPT/SettingUp_GPT.html>.

Before anything else:
$ ./bootstrap

To build in CVS workspace:
$ ./configure --with-flavor=gcc32
$ make

To install from CVS workspace to $GLOBUS_LOCATION:
$ make install

To build binary packages from CVS workspace, after installing in
$GLOBUS_LOCATION:
$ $GPT_LOCATION/sbin/globus-build gcc32

To build source packages from CVS workspace:
$ make dist

To make a source bundle, first setup a subdirectory named src-packages
with all the needed source packages (Globus and MyProxy):
$ ls -l src-packages
