Then, build a source bundle in the current working directory with:
$ $GPT_LOCATION/sbin/gpt-bundle -srcdir=src-packages myproxy globus_core_setup globus_ssl_utils_setup -output=myproxy_bundle-1.0-src.tar.gz

To build a binary bundle, first setup a subdirectory named
bin-packages with all the needed binary packages (Globus and MyProxy).
Then, build a binary bundle in the current working directory with:
$ $GPT_LOCATION/sbin/gpt-bundle -bindir=bin-packages myproxy-noflavor_data myproxy-gcc32_dev myproxy-gcc32_pgm myproxy-gcc32_rtl -output=myproxy_bundle-1.0-i686-pc-linux-gnu-gcc32.tar.gz
